Hamblett's Caravan Site is a permanent site for "travelling Families". Caravans come and go but there are a few families who stay all the time.
This is an interview with a ten year old girl from the site:
{"I've lived here for nine years, {since I was a baby.....I've got three {brothers and we sleep in two bedrooms {in our caravan...my little brother {sleeps with my mam and dad...We've got {four horses,two mares and two foals, {two dogs and a chicken...We all go to {school every day... and I go to {dancing class on Saturday mornings... {We're going to get a house soon." }
